### 2. Modern Material Effects System

Implement these **essential visual effects** in C using nxcrender:

#### A. Glass Effect (Glassmorphism)
```c
typedef struct {
    float blur_radius;      // Background blur amount (0-50)
    float opacity;          // Glass opacity (0.0-1.0)
    float refraction;       // Light refraction intensity
    vec4 tint_color;        // Glass tint (RGBA)
    float border_opacity;   // Border/edge visibility
} GlassEffect;

// Rendering pipeline:
// 1. Render layers below to offscreen buffer
// 2. Apply gaussian blur to buffer
// 3. Composite with transparency and tint
// 4. Add subtle specular highlights
// 5. Apply border/edge glow
```

#### B. Frosted Glass Effect
```c
typedef struct {
    float frost_intensity;  // Frost pattern strength (0-100)
    float blur_radius;      // Background blur (0-30)
    float grain_size;       // Noise/grain detail
    float opacity;          // Overall opacity
    vec4 frost_color;       // Frost tint color
} FrostEffect;

// Rendering approach:
// 1. Apply procedural noise pattern
// 2. Gaussian blur background
// 3. Overlay frost texture
// 4. Color grading and tint
```

#### C. Tilt-Shift Effect
```c
typedef struct {
    vec2 focus_point;       // Center of sharp focus (x, y)
    float focus_radius;     // Sharp region size
    float blur_strength;    // Out-of-focus blur amount
    float falloff;          // Gradient falloff rate
    float angle;            // Tilt angle (0-360°)
} TiltShiftEffect;

// Implementation:
// 1. Create depth/distance map from focus point
// 2. Apply variable gaussian blur based on distance
// 3. Handle elliptical/angled focus regions
// 4. Optimize for real-time preview
```

#### D. Orb/Sphere Effect
```c
typedef struct {
    vec3 light_position;    // 3D light source position
    float specularity;      // Specular highlight strength
    float metalness;        // Metallic surface property
    float roughness;        // Surface roughness (0=smooth, 1=rough)
    vec4 base_color;        // Surface base color
    float ambient_occlusion; // Cavity darkening
} OrbEffect;

// Rendering technique:
// 1. Calculate surface normals for sphere geometry
// 2. Implement Phong/PBR lighting model
// 3. Generate specular highlights
// 4. Add ambient occlusion in crevices
// 5. Apply environmental reflections
```

#### E. Additional Modern Effects
```c
// 1. Gradient Mesh
// 2. Inner/Outer Glow (customizable)
// 3. Drop Shadow (soft, realistic)
// 4. Depth of Field blur
// 5. Chromatic Aberration
// 6. Light Rays/God Rays
// 7. Caustics (light through water/glass)
// 8. Iridescence/Holographic
```

