## Code Quality Requirements

```c
// Follow these standards:

// 1. Memory management
- Always free allocated resources
- Use RAII-style patterns where possible
- Avoid memory leaks (use Valgrind for testing)

// 2. Error handling
- Check all allocation results
- Proper error propagation
- Graceful degradation

// 3. Performance
- Profile hot paths (gprof, perf)
- Minimize allocations in render loop
- Use SIMD where beneficial (SSE, AVX)

// 4. Code style
- Clear function names
- Comprehensive comments for complex algorithms
- Consistent formatting
- Modular, reusable components
```

